The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 World Briefs

 Civilians killed 

 Kandahar, June 22 (Reuters): An air strike by foreign-led forces killed 25 civilians, including 12 members of a family, and 20 Taliban fighters in southern Afghanistan, a police chief said today. 

 Helmand provincial police chief Hussien Andiwal said the raid took place on Thursday night. 

 Blair religion 

 London (Reuters): Prime Minister Tony Blair will meet Pope Benedict at the Vatican on Saturday to prepare to convert to Roman Catholicism. 




